Class EffortEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • management.Entry
      • management.EffortEntry

  • public class EffortEntry
extends Entry
    The EffortEntry class stores effort information that belong to a module.

    It is an extension of the Entry class.

    This class is actually a wrapper class for multiple SelfStudy objects, that receive additional information. This wrapping makes it possible to access and handle the information in a more sophisticated manner.

    Several Constructors are given, but only a few are useful. Use only Constructors that are marked as "useful". All other Constructors are used for test purposes.

        Creates an EffortEntry with given parameters. (Overloaded)

        Is used to create new EffortEntries. e.g. a Module needs to be modified or is created from scratch. The super class is initialized with default values for new Entry.
